* Data Quality
** Definition
***[#white] ====<size:15>**Data Quality** refers to the "state of data" in terms of "accuracy, completeness, consistency, reliability", and other factors that determine its "usefulness" for "decision-making and analysis".

** Key Concepts
***[#white] ====<size:14>Accuracy
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Data correctness and precision.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Completeness
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Data comprehensiveness without missing values.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Consistency
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Uniformity and coherence of data across sources.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Reliability
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Data trustworthiness and source credibility.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Timeliness
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Data relevance within acceptable timeframes.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Relevance
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Data applicability to the intended purpose.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Validity
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Data conformity to predefined rules and constraints.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Data Cleansing
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>The process of correcting and removing errors from data.
***[#white] ====<size:14>Data Profiling
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Analyzing data to understand its quality and characteristics.

